in Biron]] 16 saves / 19 shots\n|goalie3-2   =[[Cristobal Huet]] 27 saves / 32 shots\n\n|date4       =April 17\n|score4      =3\u20134\n|ot4         =2\n|won4        =1\n|recap4      =www.nhl.com/scores/htmlreports/20072008/GS030134.HTM\n|4-1-1       =00:42 \u2013 [[Jeff Carter]] (2)<br>18:33 \u2013 Jeff Carter (3)\n|4-1-2       =[[Nicklas B\u00e4ckstr\u00f6m|Nicklas Backstrom]] (1) \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 02:41<br>[[Alexander Semin]] (1) \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 12:59\n|4-2-1       =''No scoring''\n|4-2-2       =[[Steve Eminger]] (1) \u2013 05:56\n|4-3-1       =10:01 \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 [[Daniel Bri\u00e8re|Daniel Briere]] (5)\n|4-3-2       =''No scoring''\n|4-4-1       =06:40 \u2013 [[Mike Knuble]] (2)\n|4-4-2       =''No scoring''\n|goalie4-1   =[[Martin Biron]] 38 saves / 41 shots\n|goalie4-2   =[[Cristobal Huet]] 42 saves / 46 shots\n\n|date5       =April 19\n|score5      =2\u20133\n|won5        =2\n|recap5      =www.nhl.com/scores/htmlreports/20072008/GS030135.HTM\n|5-1-1       =''No scoring''\n|5-1-2       =07:31 \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 [[Nicklas B\u00e4ckstr\u00f6m|Nicklas Backstrom]] (2)\n|5-2-1       =[[V\u00e1clav Prospal|Vaclav Prospal]] (3) \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 12:35\n|5-2-2       =01:25 \u2013 [[Sergei Fedorov]] (1)\n|5-3-1       =[[Derian Hatcher]] (1) \u2013 15:17\n|5-3-2       =14:33 \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 [[Alexander Semin]] (2)\n|goalie5-1   =[[Martin Biron]] 23 saves / 26 shots\n|goalie5-2   =[[Cristobal Huet]] 30 saves / 32 shots\n\n|date6       =April 21\n|score6      =4\u20132\n|won6        =2\n|recap6      =www.nhl.com/scores/htmlreports/20072008/GS030136.HTM\n|6-1-1       =03:49 \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 [[Mike Richards]] (2)\n|6-1-2       =''No scoring''\n|6-2-1       =01:18 \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 [[Daniel Bri\u00e8re|Daniel Briere]] (6)\n|6-2-2       =[[Nicklas B\u00e4ckstr\u00f6m|Nicklas Backstrom]] (3) \u2013 09:34<br>[[Alexander Semin]] (3) \u2013 18:03\n|6-3-1       =''No scoring''\n|6-3-2       =[[Alexander Ovechkin]] (2) \u2013 02:46<br>Alexander Ovechkin (3) \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 10:41\n|goalie6-1   =[[Martin Biron]] 36 saves / 40 shots\n|goalie6-2   =[[Cristobal Huet]] 33 saves / 35 shots\n\n|date7       =April 22\n|score7      =3\u20132\n|ot7         =1\n|won7        =1\n|recap7      =www.nhl.com/scores/htmlreports/20072008/GS030137.HTM\n|7-1-1       =[[Scottie Upshall]] (1) \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 15:38\n|7-1-2       =05:42 \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 [[Nicklas B\u00e4ckstr\u00f6m|Nicklas Backstrom]] (4)\n|7-2-1       =[[Sami Kapanen]] (2) \u2013 09:47\n|7-2-2       =15:29 \u2013 [[Alexander Ovechkin]] (4)\n|7-3-1       =''No scoring''\n|7-3-2       =''No scoring''\n|7-4-1       =[[Joffrey Lupul]] (1) \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 06:06\n|7-4-2       =''No scoring''\n|goalie7-1   =[[Martin Biron]] 39 saves / 41 shots\n|goalie7-2   =[[Cristobal Huet]] 31 saves / 34 shots\n\n|series = Philadelphia won series 4\u20133\n}}\n\n====(4) New Jersey Devils vs. (5) New York Rangers====\n\nThe New Jersey Devils entered the playoffs as the fourth seed in the Eastern Conference with 99 points. New York qualified as the fifth seed earning 97 points during the regular season. This was the fifth playoff meeting between these two teams, with the Rangers winning three of the four previous series. They last met in the [[2006 Stanley Cup playoffs|2006 Eastern Conference Quarterfinals]] where New Jersey won in four games. New York won seven of the eight games during this year's regular season series.\n\nThe Rangers defeated the Devils in five games. [[Scott Gomez]] had three assists in game one as the Rangers won 4\u20131. New York scored twice in 23 seconds to break a scoreless tie in the third period of game two and [[Henrik Lundqvist]] allowed one goal against for the second consecutive game as the Rangers took a 2\u20130 series lead. During the second period of game three while on a two-man advantage, the Rangers' [[Sean Avery]] tried to screen New Jersey goaltender [[Martin Brodeur]] by waving his hands and stick while facing Brodeur. Devils forward [[John Madden (ice hockey)|John Madden]] ended the game at 6:01 of the first overtime in a 4\u20133 New Jersey victory. After the game the NHL issued an interpretation of the League's rules, stating that an unsportsmanlike conduct minor penalty would be called on actions such as the one used by Avery.<ref name=\"ESPNAmendedRule\"/> [[Marc Staal]] broke a 3\u20133 tie for the Rangers late in third period of game four as New York took a 3\u20131 series lead. Rangers forward [[Jarom\u00edr J\u00e1gr|Jaromir Jagr]] had a goal and two assists as New York finished off the Devils in game five with a 5\u20133 win.\n\n{{NHLPlayoffs\n|team1=New York Rangers\n|team2=New Jersey Devils\n|stadium2=[[Madison Square Garden]]\n|stadium1=[[Prudential Center]]\n\n|date1       =April 9\n|score1      =4\u20131\n|won1        =1\n|recap1      =www.nhl.com/scores/htmlreports/20072008/GS030141.HTM\n|1-1-1       =''No scoring''\n|1-1-2       =''No scoring''\n|1-2-1       =[[Brendan Shanahan]] (1) \u2013 01:45\n|1-2-2       =14:14 \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 [[Paul Martin (ice hockey)|Paul Martin]] (1)\n|1-3-1       =[[Ryan Callahan]] (1) \u2013 ''sh'' \u2013 07:23<br>[[Sean Avery]] (1) \u2013 17:07<br>[[Nigel Dawes]] (1) \u2013 ''en'' \u2013 19:55\n|1-3-2       =''No scoring''\n|goalie1-1   =[[Henrik Lundqvist]] 26 saves / 27 shots\n|goalie1-2   =[[Martin Brodeur]] 24 saves / 27 shots\n\n|date2       =April 11\n|score2      =2\u20131\n|won2        =1\n|recap2      =www.nhl.com/scores/htmlreports/20072008/GS030142.HTM\n|2-1-1       =''No scoring''\n|2-1-2       =''No scoring''\n|2-2-1       =''No scoring''\n|2-2-2       =''No scoring''\n|2-3-1       =[[Jarom\u00edr J\u00e1gr|Jaromir Jagr]] (1) \u2013 04:26<br>[[Sean Avery]] (2) \u2013 04:49\n|2-3-2       =18:37 \u2013 [[John Madden (ice hockey)|John Madden]] (1)\n|goalie2-1   =[[Henrik Lundqvist]] 26 saves / 27 shots\n|goalie2-2   =[[Martin Brodeur]] 28 saves / 30 shots\n\n|date3       =April 13\n|score3      =4\u20133\n|ot3         =1\n|won3