 Minnesota won in seven games. Minnesota won five of the eight games during this year's regular season series.\n\nThe Avalanche eliminated the Wild in six games. Colorado captain [[Joe Sakic]] added to his own league record in game one as he scored his eighth and final career playoff overtime goal in a 3\u20132 victory. The teams traded goals in the final two minutes of regulation in game two before [[Keith Carney]] ended the game 1:14 into the first overtime period, as the Wild evened the series with a 3\u20132 win. [[Pierre-Marc Bouchard]] scored the overtime winner in game three for Minnesota at 11:58 in the third consecutive overtime game of this series. Five different Colorado players scored in game four as the Avalanche forced Wild goaltender [[Niklas B\u00e4ckstr\u00f6m|Niklas Backstrom]] from the game, winning 5\u20131. Colorado goaltender [[Jos\u00e9 Th\u00e9odore|Jose Theodore]] made 38 saves in a 3\u20132 game five win. Theodore continued his strong play in game six as he made 34 saves from 35 shots against as Colorado closed out the series with a 2\u20131 victory.\n\t\n{{NHLPlayoffs\n|team1=Colorado Avalanche\n|team2=Minnesota Wild\n|stadium2=[[Pepsi Center]]\n|stadium1=[[Xcel Energy Center]]\n\n|date1       =April 9\n|score1      =3\u20132\n|ot1         =1\n|won1        =1\n|recap1      =www.nhl.com/scores/htmlreports/20072008/GS030171.HTM\n|1-1-1       =''No scoring''\n|1-1-2       =''No scoring''\n|1-2-1       =[[Kurt Sauer]] (1) \u2013 01:29<br>[[Ryan Smyth]] (1) \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 13:08\n|1-2-2       =''No scoring''\n|1-3-1       =''No scoring''\n|1-3-2       =03:02 \u2013 [[Mikko Koivu]] (1)<br>06:13 \u2013 [[Todd Fedoruk]] (1)\n|1-4-1       =[[Joe Sakic]] (1) \u2013 11:11\n|1-4-2       =''No scoring''\n|goalie1-1   =[[Jos\u00e9 Th\u00e9odore|Jose Theodore]] 28 saves / 30 shots\n|goalie1-2   =[[Niklas B\u00e4ckstr\u00f6m|Niklas Backstrom]] 19 saves / 22 shots\n\n|date2       =April 11\n|score2      =2\u20133\n|ot2         =1\n|won2        =2\n|re