''\n|goalie4-1   =[[Henrik Lundqvist]] 29 saves / 29 shots\n|goalie4-2   =[[Marc-Andr\u00e9 Fleury|Marc-Andre Fleury]] 20 saves / 22 shots\n\n|date5       =May 4\n|score5      =2\u20133\n|ot5         =1\n|won5        =2\n|recap5      =www.nhl.com/scores/htmlreports/20072008/GS030225.HTM\n|5-1-1       =''No scoring''\n|5-1-2       =''No scoring''\n|5-2-1       =''No scoring''\n|5-2-2       =08:45 \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 [[Mari\u00e1n Hossa|Marian Hossa]] (4)<br>12:40 \u2013 [[Evgeni Malkin]] (6)\n|5-3-1       =[[Lauri Korpikoski]] (1) \u2013 02:03<br>[[Nigel Dawes]] (2) \u2013 03:25\n|5-3-2       =''No scoring''\n|5-4-1       =''No scoring''\n|5-4-2       =07:10 \u2013 Marian Hossa (5)\n|goalie5-1   =[[Henrik Lundqvist]] 37 saves / 40 shots\n|goalie5-2   =[[Marc-Andr\u00e9 Fleury|Marc-Andre Fleury]] 20 saves / 22 shots\n\n|series = Pittsburgh won series 4\u20131\n}}\n\n===Western Conference Semifinals===\n\n====(1) Detroit Red Wings vs. (6) Colorado Avalanche====\n\nThis was the sixth playoff meeting between these two teams, with Colorado winning three of the five previous series. They last met in the [[2002 Stanley Cup playoffs|2002 Western Conference Finals]] where Detroit won in seven games. Detroit swept this year's four game regular season series.\n\nThe Red Wings swept the Avalanche in four games. Avalanche goaltender [[Jos\u00e9 Th\u00e9odore|Jose Theodore]] was pulled early in the second period of game one after allowing four goals on 16 shots; the Red Wings held on to win 4\u20133. Detroit forward [[Johan Franz\u00e9n|Johan Franzen]]'s hat trick in game two helped the Red Wings to a 5\u20131 victory. [[Henrik Zetterberg]]'s power-play goal just past the midway mark of the second period held up as the game-winner for Detroit in game three. After allowing the tying goal early in the first period of game four, the Red Wings scored the next seven goals and easily eliminated the Avalanche with an 8\u20132 win.\n\n{{NHLPlayoffs\n|team1=Colorado Avalanche\n|team2=Detroit Red Wings\n|stadium2=[[Pepsi Center]]\n|stadium1=[[Joe Louis Arena]]\n\n|date1       =April 24\n|score1      =3\u20134\n|won1        =2\n|recap1      =www.nhl.com/scores/htmlreports/20072008/GS030231.HTM\n|1-1-1       =[[Paul Stastny]] (2) \u2013 08:53\n|1-1-2       =09:46 \u2013 [[Henrik Zetterberg]] (3)<br>13:48 \u2013 [[Daniel Cleary]] (1)<br>17:23 \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 [[Johan Franz\u00e9n|Johan Franzen]] (3)\n|1-2-1       =[[John-Michael Liles]] (1) \u2013 05:17<br>[[Milan Hejduk]] (3) \u2013 16:29\n|1-2-2       =01:13 \u2013 Johan Franzen (4)\n|1-3-1       =''No scoring''\n|1-3-2       =''No scoring''\n|goalie1-1   =[[Jos\u00e9 Th\u00e9odore|Jose Theodore]] 12 saves / 16 shots<br>[[Peter Budaj]] 20 saves / 20 shots\n|goalie1-2   =[[Chris Osgood]] 18 saves / 21 shots\n\n|date2       =April 26\n|score2      =1\u20135\n|won2        =2\n|recap2      =www.nhl.com/scores/htmlreports/20072008/GS030232.HTM\n|2-1-1       =''No scoring''\n|2-1-2       =04:22 \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 [[Johan Franz\u00e9n|Johan Franzen]] (5)\n|2-2-1       =''No scoring''\n|2-2-2       =04:04 \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 Johan Franzen (6)<br>05:42 \u2013 [[Valtteri Filppula]] (2)<br>10:11 \u2013 [[Henrik Zetterberg]] (4)\n|2-3-1       =[[Ian Laperri\u00e8re|Ian Laperriere]] (1) \u2013 02:38\n|2-3-2       =08:47 \u2013 ''sh'' \u2013 Johan Franzen (7)\n|goalie2-1   =[[Jos\u00e9 Th\u00e9odore|Jose Theodore]] 16 saves / 20 shots<br>[[Peter Budaj]] 19 saves / 20 shots\n|goalie2-2   =[[Chris Osgood]] 19 saves / 20 shots\n\n|date3       =April 29\n|score3      =4\u20133\n|won3        =2\n|recap3      =www.nhl.com/scores/htmlreports/20072008/GS030233.HTM\n|3-1-1       =05:17 \u2013 [[Cody McLeod]] (1)\n|3-1-2       =[[Pavel Datsyuk]] (4) \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 12:14<br>[[Johan Franz\u00e9n|Johan Franzen]] (8) \u2013 13:12\n|3-2-1       =08:08 \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 [[Andrew Brunette]] (4)\n|3-2-2       =Pavel Datsyuk (5) \u2013 06:36<br>[[Henrik Zetterberg]] (5) \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 12:24\n|3-3-1       =05:19 \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 Andrew Brunette (5)\n|3-3-2       =''No scoring''\n|goalie3-1   =[[Jos\u00e9 Th\u00e9odore|Jose Theodore]] 31 saves / 35 shots\n|goalie3-2   =[[Chris Osgood]] 30 saves / 33 shots\n\n|date4       =May 1\n|score4      =8\u20132\n|won4        =2\n|recap4      =www.nhl.com/scores/htmlreports/20072008/GS030234.HTM\n|4-1-1       =06:51 \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 [[Tyler Arnason]] (2)\n|4-1-2       =[[Mikael Samuelsson]] (1) \u2013 04:33<br>[[Tomas Holmstr\u00f6m|Tomas Holmstrom]] (2) \u2013 18:34<br>[[Johan Franz\u00e9n|Johan Franzen]] (9) \u2013 19:21\n|4-2-1       =''No scoring''\n|4-2-2       =[[Henrik Zetterberg]] (6) \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 02:15<br>Henrik Zetterberg (7) \u2013 05:45<br>Johan Franzen (10) \u2013 ''sh'' \u2013 11:37<br>Johan Franzen (11) \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 17:15\n|4-3-1       =10:26 \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 [[John-Michael Liles]] 2\n|4-3-2       =Mikael Samuelsson (2) \u2013 08:02\n|goalie4-1   =[[Jos\u00e9 Th\u00e9odore|Jose Theodore]] 12 saves / 15 shots<br>[[Peter Budaj]] 20 saves / 25 shots\n|goalie4-2   =[[Chris Osgood]] 29 saves / 31 shots\n\n|series = Detroit won series 4\u20130\n}}\n\n====(2) San Jose Sharks vs. (5) Dallas Stars====\n\nThis was the third playoff meeting between these two teams, with Dallas winning both of the previous series. They last met in the [[2000 Stanley Cup playoffs|2000 Western Conference Semifinals]] where Dallas won in five games. Dallas won this year's eight-game regular season series earning ten of sixteen points.\n\nThe Stars held on to defeat the Sharks in six games. [[Jonathan Cheechoo]] tied game one late in the third period for San Jose, but Dallas captain [[Brenden Morrow]] scored 4:39 into the first overtime to give Dallas a 3\u20132 victory. Dallas forward [[Brad Richards]] keyed a four-goal outburst in the third period of game two by scoring a goal and three assists to lead the Stars to a 5\u20132 win. In game three the Stars overcame a one-goal deficit in the third period as they won in the first overtime on a goal from defenceman [[Mattias Norstr\u00f6m|Mattias Norstrom]] at 4:37. [[Milan Mich\u00e1lek|Milan Michalek]] broke the tie for San Jose in game four with his power-play goal at 3:26 of the third period as the Sharks avoided elimination with a 2\u20131 victory. Dallas took a two-goal lead into the third period of game five, however, the Sharks tied the game with goals by Milan Michalek and [[Brian Campbell]]. Overtime was needed for the third time in five games and just 1:05 into the first overtime San Jose forward [[Joe Pavelski]] converted on a turnover to keep the Sharks alive with a 3\u20132 win. After trading goals in regulation time, game six became the [[Overtime (ice hockey)#Longest NHL overtime games|eighth-longest game in NHL history]] as Brenden Morrow tipped home a pass on the power-play from defenceman [[St\u00e9phane Robidas|Stephane Robidas]] to end the game 9:03 into the fourth overtime period and win the series for the Stars 4\u20132.\n\n{{NHLPlayoffs\n|team1=Dallas Stars\n|team2=San Jose Sharks\n|stadium2=[[American Airlines Center]]\n|stadium1=[[HP Pavilion at San Jose|HP Pavilion]]\n\n|date1       =April 25\n|score1      =3\u20132\n|ot1         =1\n|won1        =1\n|recap1      =www.nhl.com/scores/htmlreports/20072008/GS030241.HTM\n|1-1-1       =''No scoring''\n|1-1-2       =''No scoring''\n|1-2-1       =[[Mike Modano]] (3) \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 06:06<br>[[Brenden Morrow]] (4) \u2013 09:09\n|1-2-2       =04:50 \u2013 [[Milan Mich\u00e1lek|Milan Michalek]] (1)\n|1-3-1       =''No scoring''\n|1-3-2       =16:58 \u2013 [[Jonathan Cheechoo]] (4)\n|1-4-1       =Brenden Morrow (5) \u2013 04:39\n|1-4-2       =''No scoring''\n|goalie1-1   =[[Marty Turco]] 25 saves / 27 shots\n|goalie1-2   =[[Evgeni Nabokov]] 15 saves / 18 shots\n\n|date2       =April 27\n|score2      =5\u20132\n|won2        =1\n|recap2      =www.nhl.com/scores/htmlreports/20072008/GS030242.HTM\n|2-1-1       =[[Mike Ribeiro]] (3) \u2013 15:37\n|2-1-2       =10:13 \u2013 