|Tim Thomas]] 27 saves / 28 shots\n|goalie4-2   =[[Carey Price]] 27 saves / 27 shots\n\n|date5       =April 17\n|score5      =5\u20131\n|won5        =1\n|recap5      =www.nhl.com/ice/recap.htm?id=2007030115\n|5-1-1       =''No scoring''\n|5-1-2       =09:47 \u2013 [[Alexei Kovalev]] (2)\n|5-2-1       =[[Phil Kessel]] (1) \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 07:45\n|5-2-2       =''No scoring''\n|5-3-1       =[[Glen Metropolit]] (1) \u2013 03:31<br>[[Zdeno Ch\u00e1ra|Zdeno Chara]] (1) \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 05:49<br>[[Marco Sturm]] (1) \u2013 ''sh'' \u2013 15:13<br>[[Vladim\u00edr Sobotka|Vladimir Sobotka]] (1) \u2013 17:48\n|5-3-2       =''No scoring''\n|goalie5-1   =[[Tim Thomas (ice hockey)|Tim Thomas]] 31 saves / 32 shots\n|goalie5-2   =[[Carey Price]] 19 saves / 24 shots\n\n|date6       =April 19\n|score6      =4\u20135\n|won6        =1\n|recap6      =www.nhl.com/ice/recap.htm?id=2007030116\n|6-1-1       =''No scoring''\n|6-1-2       =[[Chris Higgins (ice hockey)|Chris Higgins]] (1) \u2013 09:44\n|6-2-1       =01:54 \u2013 [[Phil Kessel]] (2)\n|6-2-2       =[[Tom\u00e1\u0161 Plekanec|Tomas Plekanec]] (1) \u2013 07:43\n|6-3-1       =03:13 \u2013 [[Vladim\u00edr Sobotka|Vladimir Sobotka]] (3)<br>12:13 \u2013 [[Milan Lucic]] (2)<br>15:45 \u2013 Phil Kessel (3)<br>17:23 \u2013 [[Marco Sturm]] (2)\n|6-3-2       =[[Francis Bouillon]] (1) \u2013 10:04<br>Chris Higgins (2) \u2013 15:56\n|goalie6-1   =[[Tim Thomas (ice hockey)|Tim Thomas]] 31 saves / 35 shots\n|goalie6-2   =[[Carey Price]] 31 saves / 36 shots\n\n|date7       =April 21\n|score7      =0\u20135\n|won7        =2\n|recap7      =www.nhl.com/ice/recap.htm?id=2007030117\n|7-1-1       =''No scoring''\n|7-1-2       =03:31 \u2013 [[Mike Komisarek]] (1)\n|7-2-1       =''No scoring''\n|7-2-2       =10:45 \u2013 [[Mark Streit]] (1)<br>15:13 \u2013 [[Andrei Kostitsyn]] (2)\n|7-3-1       =''No scoring''\n|7-3-2       =17:58 \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 Andrei Kostitsyn (3)<br>19:52 \u2013 [[Sergei Kostitsyn]] (3)\n|goalie7-1   =[[Tim Thomas (ice hockey)|Tim Thomas]] 30 saves / 35 shots\n|goalie7-2   =[[Carey Price]] 25 saves / 25 shots\n\n|series = Montreal won series 4\u20133\n}}\n\n====(2) Pittsburgh Penguins vs. (7) Ottawa Senators====\n\nThe Pittsburgh Penguins entered the playoffs as the Atlantic Division champions, earning the second seed in the Eastern Conference with 102 points. Ottawa qualified as the seventh seed earning 94 points (winning the tie-breaker in total wins with Boston) during the regular season. This was the second playoff meeting between these two teams, with Ottawa winning the only previous series. They last met in the [[2007 Stanley Cup playoffs|previous year's Eastern Conference Quarterfinals]] where Ottawa won in five games. Ottawa won three of the four games during this year's regular season series.\n\nThe Penguins swept the Senators in four games. [[Marc-Andr\u00e9 Fleury|Marc-Andre Fleury]] made 26 saves and [[Gary Roberts (ice hockey)|Gary Roberts]] scored twice as the Penguins won game one by a score of 4\u20130. Penguins forward [[Ryan Malone]] put Pittsburgh ahead again in game two after they blew a three-goal lead earlier in the game with a power-play goal at 18:58 of the third period; the Penguins held on for a 5\u20133 victory. [[Sidney Crosby]]'s goal in the opening seconds of the third period of game three broke a 1\u20131 tie as Pittsburgh eventually won 4\u20131. Pittsburgh completed the series sweep in game four with a 3\u20131 win.\n\t\n{{NHLPlayoffs\n|team1=Ottawa Senators\n|team2=Pittsburgh Penguins\n|stadium2=[[Scotiabank Place]]\n|stadium1=[[Mellon Arena]]\n\n|date1       =April 9\n|score1      =0\u20134\n|won1        =2\n|recap1      =www.nhl.com/ice/recap.htm?id=2007030121\n|1-1-1       =''No scoring''\n|1-1-2       =01:08 \u2013 [[Gary Roberts (ice hockey)|Gary Roberts]] (1)<br>12:28 \u2013 [[Petr S\u00fdkora|Petr Sykora]] (1)\n|1-2-1       =''No scoring''\n|1-2-2       =''No scoring''\n|1-3-1       =''No scoring''\n|1-3-2       =13:58 \u2013 [[Evgeni Malki