ce hockey)|John Madden]] ended the game at 6:01 of the first overtime in a 4\u20133 New Jersey victory. After the game the NHL issued an interpretation of the League's rules, stating that an unsportsmanlike conduct minor penalty would be called on actions such as the one used by Avery.<ref name=\"ESPNAmendedRule\"/> [[Marc Staal]] broke a 3\u20133 tie for the Rangers late in third period of game four as New York took a 3\u20131 series lead. Rangers forward [[Jarom\u00edr J\u00e1gr|Jaromir Jagr]] had a goal and two assists as New York finished off the Devils in game five with a 5\u20133 win.\n\n{{NHLPlayoffs\n|team1=New York Rangers\n|team2=New Jersey Devils\n|stadium2=[[Madison Square Garden]]\n|stadium1=[[Prudential Center]]\n\n|date1       =April 9\n|score1      =4\u20131\n|won1        =1\n|recap1      =www.nhl.com/scores/htmlreports/20072008/GS030141.HTM\n|1-1-1       =''No scoring''\n|1-1-2       =''No scoring''\n|1-2-1       =[[Brendan Shanahan]] (1) \u2013 01:45\n|1-2-2       =14:14 \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 [[Paul Martin (ice hockey)|Paul Martin]] (1)\n|1-3-1       =[[Ryan Callahan]] (1) \u2013 ''sh'' \u2013 07:23<br>[[Sean Avery]] (1) \u2013 17:07<br>[[Nigel Dawes]] (1) \u2013 ''en'' \u2013 19:55\n|1-3-2       =''No scoring''\n|goalie1-1   =[[Henrik Lundqvist]] 26 saves / 27 shots\n|goalie1-2   =[[Martin Brodeur]] 24 saves / 27 shots\n\n|date2       =April 11\n|score2      =2\u20131\n|won2        =1\n|recap2      =www.nhl.com/scores/htmlreports/20072008/GS030142.HTM\n|2-1-1       =''No scoring''\n|2-1-2       =''No scoring''\n|2-2-1       =''No scoring''\n|2-2-2       =''No scoring''\n|2-3-1       =[[Jarom\u00edr J\u00e1gr|Jaromir Jagr]] (1) \u2013 04:26<br>[[Sean Avery]] (2) \u2013 04:49\n|2-3-2       =18:37 \u2013 [[John Madden (ice hockey)|John Madden]] (1)\n|goalie2-1   =[[Henrik Lundqvist]] 26 saves / 27 shots\n|goalie2-2   =[[Martin Brodeur]] 28 saves / 30 shots\n\n|date3       =April 13\n|score3      =4\u20133\n|ot3         =1\n|won3        =2\n|recap3    