ron]] made 36 saves as the Flyers won game four 4\u20132. Flyers forward [[Scottie Upshall]] broke the tie in game five as he scored the series-clinching goal with just over three minutes remaining in regulation time as Philadelphia earned a 6\u20134 victory.\n\n{{NHLPlayoffs\n|team1=Philadelphia Flyers\n|team2=Montreal Canadiens\n|stadium2=[[Wachovia Center]]\n|stadium1=[[Bell Centre]]\n\n|date1       =April 24\n|score1      =3\u20134\n|ot1         =1\n|won1        =2\n|recap1      =www.nhl.com/scores/htmlreports/20072008/GS030211.HTM\n|1-1-1       =[[R. J. Umberger]] (2) \u2013 13:15<br>[[Jim Dowd (ice hockey)|Jim Dowd]] (1) \u2013 16:49\n|1-1-2       =''No scoring''\n|1-2-1       =''No scoring''\n|1-2-2       =09:44 \u2013 [[Andrei Kostitsyn]] (4)<br>16:03 \u2013 ''sh'' \u2013 [[Alexei Kovalev]] (3)\n|1-3-1       =[[Joffrey Lupul]] (2) \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 00:19\n|1-3-2       =19:31 \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 Alexei Kovalev (4)\n|1-4-1       =''No scoring''\n|1-4-2       =00:48 \u2013 [[Tom Kostopoulos]] (3)\n|goalie1-1   =[[Martin Biron]] 30 saves / 34 shots\n|goalie1-2   =[[Carey Price]] 30 saves / 33 shots\n\n|date2       =April 26\n|score2      =4\u20132\n|won2        =1\n|recap2      =www.nhl.com/scores/htmlreports/20072008/GS030212.HTM\n|2-1-1       =[[R. J. Umberger]] (3) \u2013 05:53<br>[[Jeff Carter]] (4) \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 08:39\n|2-1-2       =16:18 \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 [[Saku Koivu]] (1)\n|2-2-1       =[[Daniel Bri\u00e8re|Daniel Briere]] (7) \u2013 13:33\n|2-2-2       =''No scoring''\n|2-3-1       =R. J. Umberger (4) \u2013 17:39\n|2-3-2       =01:26 \u2013 [[Andrei Markov (ice hockey)|Andrei Markov]] (1)\n|goalie2-1   =[[Martin Biron]] 34 saves / 36 shots\n|goalie2-2   =[[Carey Price]] 19 saves / 23 shots\n\n|date3       =April 28\n|score3      =2\u20133\n|won3        =1\n|recap3      =www.nhl.com/scores/htmlreports/20072008/GS030213.HTM\n|3-1-1       =''No scoring''\n|3-1-2       =''No scoring''\n|3-2-1       =07:04 \u2013 [[Scottie Upshall]] (2)<br>15:12 \u2013 ''sh'' \u2013 [[Mike Richards]] (3)<br>18:19 \u2013 [[R. J. Umberger]] (5)\n|3-2-2       =''No scoring''\n|3-3-1       =''No scoring''\n|3-3-2       =[[Tom\u00e1\u0161 Plekanec|Tomas Plekanec]] (2) \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 07:29<br>[[Saku Koivu]] (2) \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 08:41\n|goalie3-1   =[[Martin Biron]] 32 saves / 34 shots\n|goalie3-2   =[[Carey Price]] 9 saves / 12 shots<br>[[Jaroslav Hal\u00e1k|Jaroslav Halak]] 2 saves / 2 shots\n\n|date4       =April 30\n|score4      =2\u20134\n|won4        =1\n|recap4      =www.nhl.com/scores/htmlreports/20072008/GS030214.HTM\n|4-1-1       =''No scoring''\n|4-1-2       =''No scoring''\n|4-2-1       =07:47 \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 [[R. J. Umberger]] (6)\n|4-2-2       =''No scoring''\n|4-3-1       =06:47 \u2013 [[Scott Hartnell]] (2)<br>16:22 \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 [[Daniel Bri\u00e8re|Daniel Briere]] (8)<br>19:58 \u2013 ''en'' \u2013 R. J. Umberger (7)\n|4-3-2       =[[Tom\u00e1\u0161 Plekanec|Tomas Plekanec]] (3) \u2013 12:59<br>[[Saku Koivu]] (3) \u2013 13:36\n|goalie4-1   =[[Martin Biron]] 36 saves / 38 shots\n|goalie4-2   =[[Jaroslav Hal\u00e1k|Jaroslav Halak]] 22 saves / 25 shots\n\n|date5       =May 3\n|score5      =6\u20134\n|won5        =1\n|recap5      =www.nhl.com/scores/htmlreports/20072008/GS030215.HTM\n|5-1-1       =[[R. J. Umberger]] (8) \u2013 10:20\n|5-1-2       =04:29 \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 [[Tom\u00e1\u0161 Plekanec|Tomas Plekanec]] (4)<br>11:28 \u2013 [[Alexei Kovalev]] (5)\n|5-2-1       =[[Mike Richards]] (4) \u2013 14:02<br>R. J. Umberger (9) \u2013 15:44<br>[[Scott Hartnell]] (3) \u2013 17:00\n|5-2-2       =08:15 \u2013 [[Chris Higgins (ice hockey)|Chris Higgins]] (3)\n|5-3-1       =[[Scottie Upshall]] (3) \u2013 16:56<br>[[Mike Knuble]] (3) \u2013 ''en'' \u2013 19:10\n|5-3-2       =02:13 \u2013 [[Andrei Kostitsyn]] (5)\n|goalie5-1   =[[Martin Biron]] 31 saves / 35 shots\n|goalie5-2   =[[Carey Price]] 31 saves / 36 shots\n\n|series = Philadelphia won series 4\u20131\n}}\n\n====(2) Pittsburgh Penguins vs. (5) New York Rangers====\n\nThis was the fourth playoff meeting between these two teams, with Pittsburgh winning all three of the previous series. They last met in the [[1996 Stanley Cup playoffs|1996 Eastern Conference Semifinals]] where Pittsburgh won in five games. New York won five of the eight games during this year's regular season series.\n\nThe Penguins defeated the Rangers in five games. The Penguins scored two goals 14 and 20 seconds apart in both the second and third periods of game one as they overcame a 3\u20130 deficit early in the second period. [[Evgeni Malkin]] scored a late power-play goal for the Penguins as they held on to win the game 5\u20134. Pittsburgh goaltender [[Marc-Andr\u00e9 Fleury|Marc-Andre Fleury]] made 26 saves to earn his second shutout of the playoffs in game two as the Penguins won 2\u20130. [[Evgeni Malkin]]'s second power-play goal of the game scored late in the second period of game three held up as the game-winning goal as the Penguins won 5\u20133. [[Henrik Lundqvist]] made 29 saves in a shutout performance as the Rangers avoided elimination with a 3\u20130 victory in game four. The Rangers battled back to tie the game early in the third period of game five, however they came up short in overtime as Pittsburgh's [[Mari\u00e1n Hossa|Marian Hossa]] scored the series-winner at 7:10 of the first overtime period to win the series for the Penguins.\n\n{{NHLPlayoffs\n|team1=New York Rangers\n|team2=Pittsburgh Penguins\n|stadium2=[[Madison Square Garden]]\n|stadium1=[[Mellon Arena]]\n\n|date1       =April 25\n|score1      =4\u20135\n|won1        =2\n|recap1      =www.nhl.com/scores/htmlreports/20072008/GS030221.HTM\n|1-1-1       =[[Martin Straka]] (2) \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 13:40\n|1-1-2       =''No scoring''\n|1-2-1       =[[Chris Drury]] (3) \u2013 01:52<br>[[Sean Avery]] (4) \u2013 03:37\n|1-2-2       =08:13 \u2013 [[Jarkko Ruutu]] (2)<br>08:27 \u2013 [[Pascal Dupuis]] (1)\n|1-3-1       =[[Scott Gomez]] (4) \u2013 10:04\n|1-3-2    