rik Lundqvist]] 29 saves / 29 shots\n|goalie4-2   =[[Marc-Andr\u00e9 Fleury|Marc-Andre Fleury]] 20 saves / 22 shots\n\n|date5       =May 4\n|score5      =2\u20133\n|ot5         =1\n|won5        =2\n|recap5      =www.nhl.com/scores/htmlreports/20072008/GS030225.HTM\n|5-1-1       =''No scoring''\n|5-1-2       =''No scoring''\n|5-2-1       =''No scoring''\n|5-2-2       =08:45 \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 [[Mari\u00e1n Hossa|Marian Hossa]] (4)<br>12:40 \u2013 [[Evgeni Malkin]] (6)\n|5-3-1       =[[Lauri Korpikoski]] (1) \u2013 02:03<br>[[Nigel Dawes]] (2) \u2013 03:25\n|5-3-2       =''No scoring''\n|5-4-1       =''No scoring''\n|5-4-2       =07:10 \u2013 Marian Hossa (5)\n|goalie5-1   =[[Henrik Lundqvist]] 37 saves / 40 shots\n|goalie5-2   =[[Marc-Andr\u00e9 Fleury|Marc-Andre Fleury]] 20 saves / 22 shots\n\n|series = Pittsburgh won series 4\u20131\n}}\n\n===Western Conference Semifinals===\n\n====(1) Detroit Red Wings vs. (6) Colorado Avalanche====\n\nThis was the sixth playoff meeting between these two teams, with Colorado winning three of the five previous series. They last met in the [[2002 Stanley Cup playoffs|2002 Western Conference Finals]] where Detroit won in seven games. Detroit swept this year's four game regular season series.\n\nThe Red Wings swept the Avalanche in four games. Avalanche goaltender [[Jos\u00e9 Th\u00e9odore|Jose Theodore]] was pulled early in the second period of game one after allowing four goals on 16 shots; the Red Wings held on to win 4\u20133. Detroit forward [[Johan Franz\u00e9n|Johan Franzen]]'s hat trick in game two helped the Red Wings to a 5\u20131 victory. [[Henrik Zetterberg]]'s power-play goal just past the midway mark of the second period held up as the game-winner for Detroit in game three. After allowing the tying goal early in the first period of game four, the Red Wings scored the next seven goals and easily eliminated the Avalanche with an 8\u20132 win.\n\n{{NHLPlayoffs\n|team1=Colorado Avalanche\n|team2=Detroit Red Wings\n|stadium2=[[Pepsi Center]]\n|stadium1=[[Joe Louis Arena]]\n\n|date1       =April 24\n|score1      =3\u20134\n|won1        =2\n|recap1      =www.nhl.com/scores/htmlreports/20072008/GS030231.HTM\n|1-1-1       =[[Paul Stastny]] (2) \u2013 08:53\n|1-1-2       =09:46 \u2013 [[Henrik Zetterberg]] (3)<br>13:48 \u2013 [[Daniel Cleary]] (1)<br>17:23 \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 [[Johan Franz\u00e9n|Johan Franzen]] (3)\n|1-2-1       =[[John-Michael Liles]] (1) \u2013 05:17<br>[[Milan Hejduk]] (3) \u2013 16:29\n|1-2-2       =01:13 \u2013 Johan Franzen (4)\n|1-3-1       =''No scoring''\n|1-3-2       =''No scoring''\n|goalie1-1   =[[Jos\u00e9 Th\u00e9odore|Jose Theodore]] 12 saves / 16 shots<br>[[Peter Budaj]] 20 saves / 20 shots\n|goalie1-2   =[[Chris Osgood]] 18 saves / 21 shots\n\n|date2       =April 26\n|score2      =1\u20135\n|won2        =2\n|recap2      =www.nhl.com/scores/htmlreports/20072008/GS030232.HTM\n|2-1-1       =''No scoring''\n|2-1-2       =04:22 \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 [[Johan Franz\u00e9n|Johan Franzen]] (5)\n|2-2-1       =''No scoring''\n|2-2-2       =04:04 \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 Johan Franzen (6)<br>05:42 \u2013 [[Valtteri Filppula]] (2)<br>10:11 \u2013 [[Henrik Zetterberg]] (4)\n|2-3-1       =[[Ian Laperri\u00e8re|Ian Laperriere]] (1) \u2013 02:38\n|2-3-2       =08:47 \u2013 ''sh'' \u2013 Johan Franzen (7)\n|goalie2-1   =[[Jos\u00e9 Th\u00e9odore|Jose Theodore]] 16 saves / 20 shots<br>[[Peter Budaj]] 19 saves / 20 shots\n|goalie2-2   =[[Chris Osgood]] 19 saves / 20 shots\n\n|date3       =April 29\n|score3      =4\u20133\n|won3        =2\n|recap3      =www.nhl.com/scores/htmlreports/20072008/GS030233.HTM\n|3-1-1       =05:17 \u2013 [[Cody McLeod]] (1)\n|3-1-2       =[[Pavel Datsyuk]] (4) \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 12:14<br>[[Johan Franz\u00e9n|Johan Franzen]] (8) \u2013 13:12\n|3-2-1       =08:08 \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 [[Andrew Brunette]] (4)\n|3-2-2       =Pavel Datsyuk (5) \u2013 06:36<br>[[Henrik Zetterberg]] (5) \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 12:24\n|3-3-1       =05:19 \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 Andrew Brunette (5)\n|3-3-2       =''No scoring''\n|goalie3-1   =[[Jos\u00e9 Th\u00e9odore|Jose Theodore]] 31 saves / 35 shots\n|goalie3-2   =[[Chris Osgood]] 30 saves / 33 shots\n\n|date4       =May 1\n|score4      =8\u20132\n|won4        =2\n|recap4      =www.nhl.com/scores/htmlreports/20072008/GS030234.HTM\n|4-1-1       =06:51 \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 [[Tyler Arnason]] (2)\n|4-1-2       =[[Mikael Samuelsson]] (1) \u2013 04:33<br>[[Tomas Holmstr\u00f6m|Tomas Holmstrom]] (2) \u2013 18:34<br>[[Johan Franz\u00e9n|Johan Franzen]] (9) \u2013 19:21\n|4-2-1       =''No scoring''\n|4-2-2       =[[Henrik Zetterberg]] (6) \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 02:15<br>Henrik Zetterberg (7) \u2013 05:45<br>Johan Franzen (10) \u2013 ''sh'' \u2013 11:37<br>Johan Franzen (11) \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 17:15\n|4-3-1       =10:26 \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 [[John-Michael Liles]] 2\n|4-3-2       =Mikael Samuelsson (2) \u2013 08:02\n|goalie4-1   =[[Jos\u00e9 Th\u00e9odore|Jose Theodore]] 12 saves / 15 shots<br>[[Peter Budaj]] 20 saves / 25 shots\n|goalie4-2   =[[Chris Osgood]] 29 saves / 31 shots\n\n|series = Detroit won series 4\u20130\n}}\n\n====(2) San Jose Sharks vs. (5) Dallas Stars====\n\nThis was the third playoff meeting between these two teams, with Dallas winning both of the previous series. They last met in the [[2000 Stanley Cup playoffs|2000 Western Conference Semifinals]] where Dallas won in five games. Dallas won this year's eight-game regular season series earning ten of sixteen points.\n\nThe Stars held on to defeat the Sharks in six games. [[Jonathan Cheechoo]] tied game one late in the third period for San Jose, but Dallas captain [[Brenden Morrow]] scored 4:39 into the first overtime to give Dallas a 3\u20132 victory. Dallas forward [[Brad Richards]] keyed a four-goal outburst in the third period of game two by scoring a goal and three assists to lead the Stars to a 5\u20132 win. In game three the Stars overcame a one-goal deficit in the third period as they won in the first overtime on a goal from defenceman [[Mattias Norstr\u00f6m|Mattias Norstrom]] at 4:37. [[Milan Mich\u00e1lek|Milan Michalek]] broke the tie for San Jose in game four with his power-play goal at 3:26 of the third period as the Sharks avoided elimination with a 2\u20131 victory. Dallas took a two-goal lead into the third period of game five, however, the Sharks tied the game with goals by Milan Michalek and [[Brian Campbell]]. Overtime was needed for the third time in five games and just 1:05 into the first overtime San Jose forward [[Joe Pavelski]] converted on a turnover to keep the Sharks alive with a 3\u20132 win. After trading goals in regulation time, game six became the [[Overtime (ice hockey)#Longest NHL overtime games|eighth-longest game in NHL history]] as Brenden Morrow tipped home a pass on the power-play from defenceman [[St\u00e9phane Robidas|Stephane Robidas]] to end the game 9:03 into the fourth overtime period and win the series for the Stars 4\u20132.\n\n{{NHLPlayoffs\n|team1=Dallas Stars\n|team2=San Jose Sharks\n|stadium2=[[American Airlines Center]]\n|stadium1=[[HP Pavilion at San Jose|HP Pavilion]]\n\n|date1       =April 25\n|score1      =3\u20132\n|ot1         =1\n|won1        =1\n|recap1      =www.nhl.com/scores/htmlreports/20072008/GS030241.HTM\n|1-1-1       =''No scoring''\n|1-1-2       =''No scoring''\n|1-2-1       =[[Mike Modano]] (3) \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 06:06<br>[[Brenden Morrow]] (4) \u2013 09:09\n|1-2-2       =04:50 \u2013 [[Milan Mich\u00e1lek|Milan Michalek]] (1)\n|1-3-1       =''No scoring''\n|1-3-2       =16:58 \u2013 [[Jonathan Cheechoo]] (4)\n|1-4-1       =Brenden Morrow (5) \u2013 04:39\n|1-4-2       =''No scoring''\n|goalie1-1   =[[Marty Turco]] 25 saves / 27 shots\n|goalie1-2   =[[Evgeni Nabokov]] 15 saves / 18 shots\n\n|date2       =April 27\n|score2      =5\u20132\n|won2        =1\n|recap2      =www.nhl.com/scores/htmlreports/20072008/GS030242.HTM\n|2-1-1       =[[Mike Ribeiro]] (3) \u2013 15:37\n|2-1-2       =10:13 \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 [[Joe Pavelski]] (4)\n|2-2-1       =''No scoring''\n|2-2-2       =14:54 \u2013 [[Milan Mich\u00e1lek|Milan Michalek]] (2)\n|2-3-1       =[[Brad Richards]] (2) \u2013 00:32<br>[[Mike Modano]] (4) \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 03:39<br>[[Niklas Hagman]] (1) \u2013 13:55<br>Niklas Hagman (2) \u2013 ''en'' \u2013 18:45\n|2-3-2       =''No scoring''\n|goalie2-1   =[[Marty Turco]] 29 saves / 31 shots\n|goalie2-2   =[[Evgeni Nabokov]] 21 saves / 25 shots\n\n|date3       =April 29\n|score3      =1\u20132\n|ot3         =1\n|won3        =1\n|recap3      =www.nhl.com/scores/htmlreports/20072008/GS030243.HTM\n|3-1-1       =''No scoring''\n|3-1-2       =[[Patrick Marleau]] (3) \u2013 ''sh'' \u2013 19:25\n|3-2-1       =''No scoring''\n|3-2-2       =''No scoring''\n|3-3-1       =00:47 \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 [[Sergei Zubov]] (1)\n|3-3-2       =''No scoring''\n|3-4-1       =04:37 \u2013 [[Mattias Norstr\u00f6m|Mattias Norstrom]] (2)\n|3-4-2       =''No scoring''\n|goalie3-1   =[[Marty Turco]] 19 saves / 20 shots\n|goalie3-2   =[[Evgeni Nabokov]] 27 saves / 29 shots\n\n|date4       =April 30\n|score4      =2\u20131\n|won4        =2\n|recap4      =www.nhl.com/scores/htmlreports/20072008/GS030244.HTM\n|4-1-1       =''No scoring''\n|4-1-2       =''No scoring''\n|4-2-1       =05:25 \u2013 [[Jere Lehtinen]] (3)\n|4-2-2       =[[Patrick Marleau]] (4) \u2013 ''sh'' \u2013 09:19\n|4-3-1       =''No scoring''\n|4-3-2       =[[Milan Mich\u00e1lek|Milan Michalek]] (3) \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 03:26\n|goalie4-1   =[[Marty Turco]] 22 saves / 24 shots\n|goalie4-2   =[[Evgeni Nabokov]] 17 saves / 18 shots\n\n|date5       =May 2\n|score5      =2\u20133\n|ot5         =1\n|won5        =2\n|recap5      =www.nhl.com/scores/htmlreports/20072008/GS030245.HTM\n|5-1-1       =''No scoring''\n|5-1-2       =''No scoring''\n|5-2-1       =[[Jere Lehtinen]] (4) \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 06:14<br>[[Brenden Morrow]] (6) \u2013 19:04\n|5-2-2       =''No scoring''\n|5-3-1       =''No scoring''\n|5-3-2       =06:20 \u2013 [[Milan Mich\u00e1lek|Milan Michalek]] (4)<br>11:07 \u2013 [[Brian Campbell]] (1)\n|5-4-1       =''No scoring''\n|5-4-2       =01:05 \u2013 [[Joe Pavelski]] (5)\n|goalie5-1   =[[Marty Turco]] 19 saves / 22 shots\n|goalie5-2   =[[Evgeni Nabokov]] 24 saves / 26 shots\n\n|date6       =May 4\n|score6      =1\u20132\n|ot6         =4\n|won6        =1\n|recap6      =www.nhl.com/scores/htmlreports/20072008/GS030246.HTM\n|6-1-1       =''No scoring''\n|6-1-2       =''No scoring''\n|6-2-1       =04:49 \u2013 [[Antti Miettinen]] (1)\n|6-2-2       =''No scoring''\n|6-3-1       =''No scoring''\n|6-3-2       =[[Ryan Clowe]] (5) \u2013 01:39\n|6-4-1       =09:03 \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 [[Brenden Morrow]] (7)\n|6-4-2       =''No scoring''\n|goalie6-1   =[[Marty Turco]] 61 saves / 62 shots\n|goalie6-2   =[[Evgeni Nabokov]] 53 saves / 55 shots\n\n|series = Dallas won series 4\u20132\n}}\n\n==Conference Finals==\n{{See also|NHL Conference Finals}}\n\n===Eastern Conference Final===\n\n====(2) Pittsburgh Penguins vs. (6) Philadelphia Flyers====\n\nThis was the fourth playoff meeting between these two teams, with Philadelphia winning all three of the previous series. They last met in the [[2000 Stanley Cup playoffs|2000 Eastern Conference Semifinals]] where Philadelphia won in six games. Pittsburgh most recently made it to the Conference Finals in [[2001 Stanley Cup playoffs|2001]], when they lost to the New Jersey Devils in five games. Philadelphia last made the Conference Finals in [[2004 Stanley Cup playoffs|2004]], where they lost in seven games to the Tampa Bay Lightning. Philadelphia won five of the eight games during this year's regular season series.\n\nThe Penguins eliminated their [[Battle of Pennsylvania|cross-state rivals]] the Flyers in five games. [[Evgeni Malkin]]'s seventh goal of the playoffs held up as the game-winner for Pittsburgh in game one as the Penguins earned a 4\u20132 win. Pittsburgh forward [[Maxime Talbot]] broke the tie in game two just before the midway mark of the third period and [[Jordan Staal]] added an empty-net goal for the Penguins to give them their second consecutive 4\u20132 victory. [[Mari\u00e1n Hossa|Marian Hossa]] scored twice in game three for the Penguins as they won the game 4\u20131 to take a commanding 3\u20130 series lead. The Flyers jumped out to a 3\u20130 lead in the first period of game four and held on to win the game 4\u20132. Marian Hossa recorded four points for Pittsburgh in game five as the Penguins won their eighth consecutive home game to advance to the [[2008 Stanley Cup Finals|Stanley Cup Finals]] by a decisive final score of 6\u20130.\n\n{{NHLPlayoffs\n|team1=Philadelphia Flyers\n|team2=Pittsburgh Penguins\n|stadium2=[[Wachovia Center]]\n|stadium1=[[Mellon Arena]]\n\n|date1       =May 9\n|score1      =2\u20134\n|won1        =2\n|recap1      =www.nhl.com/scores/htmlreports/20072008/GS030311.HTM\n|1-1-1       =[[Mike Richards]] (5) \u2013 08:30<br>Mike Richards (6) \u2013 12:50\n|1-1-2       =06:19 \u2013 [[Petr S\u00fdkora|Petr Sykora]] (5)<br>14:11 \u2013 [[Sidney Crosby]] (3)<br>19:53 \u2013 [[Evgeni Malkin]] (7)\n|1-2-1       =''No scoring''\n|1-2-2       =04:50 \u2013 ''sh'' \u2013 Evgeni Malkin (8)\n|1-3-1       =''No scoring''\n|1-3-2       =''No scoring''\n|goalie1-1   =[[Martin Biron]] 17 saves / 21 shots\n|goalie1-2   =[[Marc-Andr\u00e9 Fleury|Marc-Andre Fleury]] 26 saves / 28 shots\n\n|date2       =May 11\n|score2      =2\u20134\n|won2        =2\n|recap2      =www.nhl.com/scores/htmlreports/20072008/GS030312.HTM\n|2-1-1       =''No scoring''\n|2-1-2       =10:48 \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 [[Sidney Crosby]] (4)\n|2-2-1       =[[Jeff Carter]] (5) \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 05:46<br>[[Mike Richards]] (7) \u2013 ''sh'' \u2013 19:36\n|2-2-2       =13:43 \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 [[Mari\u00e1n Hossa|Marian Hossa]] (6)\n|2-3-1       =''No scoring''\n|2-3-2       =08:51 \u2013 [[Maxime Talbot]] (2)<br>19:31 \u2013 ''en'' \u2013 [[Jordan Staal]] (3)\n|goalie2-1   =[[Martin Biron]] 34 saves / 37 shots\n|goalie2-2   =[[Marc-Andr\u00e9 Fleury|Marc-Andre Fleury]] 30 saves / 32 shots\n\n|date3       =May 13\n|score3      =4\u20131\n|won3        =2\n|recap3      =www.nhl.com/scores/htmlreports/20072008/GS030313.HTM\n|3-1-1       =10:59 \u2013 [[R. J. Umberger]] (10)\n|3-1-2       =[[Ryan Whitney]] (1) \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 05:03<br>[[Mari\u00e1n Hossa|Marian Hossa]] (7) \u2013 07:41\n|3-2-1       =''No scoring''\n|3-2-2       =''No scoring''\n|3-3-1       =''No scoring''\n|3-3-2       =[[Ryan Malone]] (4) \u2013 09:58<br>Marian Hossa (8) \u2013 ''en'' \u2013 19:06\n|goalie3-1   =[[Martin Biron]] 21 saves / 24 shots\n|goalie3-2   =[[Marc-Andr\u00e9 Fleury|Marc-Andre Fleury]] 17 saves / 18 shots\n\n|date4       =May 15\n|score4      =2\u20134\n|won4        =1\n|recap4      =www.nhl.com/scores/htmlreports/20072008/GS030314.HTM\n|4-1-1       =08:27 \u2013 [[Joffrey Lupul]] (3)<br>11:48 \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 [[Daniel Bri\u00e8re|Daniel Briere]] (9)<br>18:50 \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 [[Jeff Carter]] (6)\n|4-1-2       =''No scoring''\n|4-2-1       =''No scoring''\n|4-2-2       =''No scoring''\n|4-3-1       =19:27 \u2013 ''en'' \u2013 Joffrey Lupul (4)\n|4-3-2       =[[Jordan Staal]] (4) \u2013 03:16<br>Jordan Staal (5) \u2013 14:11\n|goalie4-1   =[[Martin Biron]] 36 saves / 38 shots\n|goalie4-2   =[[Marc-Andr\u00e9 Fleury|Marc-Andre Fleury]] 30 saves / 33 shots\n\n|date5       =May 18\n|score5      =0\u20136\n|won5        =2\n|recap5      =www.nhl.com/scores/htmlreports/20072008/GS030315.HTM\n|5-1-1       =''No scoring''\n|5-1-2       =02:30 \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 [[Ryan Malone]] (5)<br>09:50 \u2013 [[Evgeni Malkin]] (9)\n|5-2-1       =''No scoring''\n|5-2-2       =08:24 \u2013 [[Mari\u00e1n Hossa|Marian Hossa]] (9)<br>11:42 \u2013 ''pp'' \u2013 Ryan Malone (6)<br>19:02 \u2013 [[Jordan Staal]] (6)\n|5-3-1       =''No scoring''\n|5-3-2       =04:03 \u2013 [[Pascal Dupuis]] (2)\n|goalie5-1   =[[Martin Biron]] 19 saves / 25 shots\n|goalie5-2   =[[Marc-Andr\u00e9 Fleury|Marc-Andre Fleury]] 21 saves / 21 shots\n\n|series = Pittsburgh won series 4\u20131\n}}\n\n===Western Conference Final===\n\n====(1) Detroit Red Wings vs. (5) Dallas Stars====\n\nThis was the fourth playoff meeting between these two teams, with Detroit winning all three of the previous series. They last met in the [[1998 Stanley Cup playoffs|1998 Western Conference Final]] where Detroit won in six games. This was Detroit's second consecutive Conference Finals appearance; they lost to the Anaheim Ducks in six games in the [[2007 Stanley Cup playoffs|previous year]]. Dallas last made the Conference Finals in [[2000 Stanley Cup playoffs|2000]], where they defeated the Colorado Avalanche in seven games. Detroit won three of the four games during this year's regular season series.\n\nThe Red Wings defeated the Stars in six games. Detroit scored three power-play goals as they took game one 4\u20131. Red Wings' goaltender [[Chris Osgood]] made 17 saves in game two to give Detroit a 2\u20131 win. Stars' forward [[Mike Ribeiro]] was assessed a match penalty at the end of game two for retaliating to an earlier stick infraction with a two-handed slash to Chris Osgood's chest; neither players were suspended. Detroit forward [[Pavel Datsyuk]] scored a [[hat-trick]] in game three for the Red Wings; while Osgood stopped 16 shots for the 5\u20132 win. [[Marty Turco]] made 33 saves as the Stars avoided elimination in game four winning 3\u20131. Turco continued his strong play for Dallas in game five as he stopped 38 shots in a 2\u20131 victory. The Red Wings used the strength of a three-goal first period in game six to eliminate the Stars and return to the Stanley Cup Finals for the first time since 2002.\n\n{{NHLPlayoffs\n|team1=Dallas Stars\n|team2=Detroit Red Wings\n|stadium2=[[American Airlines Center]]\n|stadium1=[[Joe Louis Arena]]\n\n|date1       =May 8\n|score1      =1\u20134\n|won1        =2\n|recap1      =www.nhl.com/scores/htmlreports/20072008/GS030321.HTM\n|1-1-1       =''No scoring''\n|1-1-2       =04:28 \u2013 